parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the driver and passengers are not provided with the necessary protection.
symptoms: No deployment of airbag during a collision
resulting in injuries or fatalities
failure of the driver's side airbag to deploy
failure of the passenger airbag to deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag can cause it to deploy improperly or not at all, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag deploys incorrectly
airbag does not deploy at all
airbag inflates but does not stay inflated
airbag causes injuries due to improper deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Leaks and Vapor Emissions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system leaks can cause pressure loss, fuel vapor emissions, and increase the risk of fire hazards, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel filler
fuel tank
or fuel return hoses
high hydrocarbon levels in the vehicle
fuel tank leaks when filling up with gas
fuel leaks from the tank/filler pipe connection when the tank is full.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine stalls after a cold start
engine hesitation or difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause damage to the engine and other components, leading to premature wear and potentially causing a fire hazard. Oil spills on the road can also pose a risk to other drivers and pedestrians.
symptoms: Oil puddles under the vehicle
oil dripping from the engine
oil stains on the garage floor or driveway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling or shut down can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine shuts down without warning
vehicle stalls while driving
loss of power
difficulty restarting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system leaks can cause fuel to leak onto the road, posing a fire hazard and environmental risk. It can also lead to poor fuel efficiency and engine performance issues.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel tank or fuel lines
bad gas mileage
fuel fumes emanating from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seat belts to lock can cause the car seat to flip when turning a corner, leading to potential injury or accidents.
symptoms: The rear seat belts will not lock
the car seat flips when turning a corner
the rear seat belts do not provide proper restraint.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy during a collision can cause injury or fatalities, as the occupants are not adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy during a collision
occupants experience injury or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seat belt buckles can cause the seat belt to become inoperative, leading to potential injury or fatalities in the event of a collision.
symptoms: Seat belt buckle fails
seat belt becomes inoperative
occupants experience injury or fatalities.
